{
  "clause": "Section 7. Dispute resolution",
  "reason": "While other clauses impose severe financial burdens, Section 7 is the most concerning because it completely strips the tenant of fundamental procedural rights. Waiving a jury trial and forcing mandatory arbitration in a jurisdiction of the landlord's choosing effectively denies the tenant any meaningful access to a fair legal forum. This clause precludes class actions, limits discovery, and can force the tenant to litigate in a distant, inconvenient venue, making it practically impossible to challenge even the most egregious landlord conduct. It is a systemic denial of justice that undermines all other protections."
}
